  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lesotho Food Insecurity 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 21 st December 2015 the Government of Lesotho declared a drought emergency and appealed for support to address the food insecurity situation. An estimated 15- 30 percent of Lesotho s population are in need of humanitarian assistance to help them cope with this acute drought situation. The IFRC launched the Lesotho Food Insecurity Appeal in 22/1/2016. The BRC are supporting this appeal with 200 000 from the Disaster Fund. In December 2016 the BRC released an additional CHF 68 431.00 of G funds to the IFRC appeal to enable LRCS to carry out the fourth and final scheduled cash transfer to 1800 households.</narrative>
  </description>
